title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set result is incorrect. It either returns the wrong data set or null result set.
OB: The data set result is incorrect or null when an invalid filter expression ('row[0] equals to 0') is set.
EB: The data set result should be correct and not null when an invalid filter expression is set.
SR: To reproduce the issue, set the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' and observe the incorrect or null data set result.
